%% Fig 4.13 — Sequence: bulk attendance -> synchronous recompute (P2)
%% Source: author, derived from attendance/* + metrics/MetricsService + MetricsEngine (ARCHITECTURE.md §6)
sequenceDiagram
    actor T as Teacher
    participant FE as Next.js (web)
    participant AC as AttendanceController
    participant AS as AttendanceService
    participant MS as MetricsService
    participant ME as MetricsEngine (pure)
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    T->>FE: mark exceptions, Save
    FE->>AC: POST /api/attendance/bulk
    AC->>AS: saveBulk(lessonId, entries)
    Note over AS,DB: single @Transactional
    loop per student entry
        AS->>DB: upsert attendance (UNIQUE student_id, lesson_id)
        AS->>MS: recompute(studentId)
        MS->>DB: load grades / attendance / behaviour / activity + active formula
        MS->>ME: compute(ComputeContext)
        ME-->>MS: ComputedMetrics (composite + norms)
        MS->>DB: upsert student_metrics + write audit_log
    end
    AS-->>AC: summary
    AC-->>FE: 200 ApiResponse
    Note over FE: SWR poll shows new composite score
